title: colour-contrast Operator
caption: colour-contrast
op-purpose: measure the contrast between pairs of colours
op-input: a selection of two or more colour values
op-output: the contrast between each colour and the colour before it

<<.from-version "5.5.0">> See ColourPalettes for background.

The <<.op colour-contrast>> operator measures the contrast between each input colour and the colour before it in the list. Given N input colours, it returns N-1 contrast values.

The contrast is calculated with the Delta Phi Star algorithm, on a scale from 0 (no contrast) to approximately 100 (black on white). Input values that cannot be parsed as colours are treated as white.

For example, this filter expression measures the contrast between black and white:

```
[[black]] [[white]] +[colour-contrast[]]
```

The result is <<.value 101.42135623730948>>.

The [[readability tests|Palette Readability Tests]] of the core palettes use this operator via the function <<.var tf.check-colour-contrast>>.

See also the following related operators:

* <<.olink colour-best-contrast>> to choose the colour that contrasts best with a target colour
